10 things about St. Jean Baptist De La salle

1.Founder of Institute of the Brothers of the Christian Schools
2.He is a saint of the Roman Catholic church and the patron saint of teachers
3.He was a priest, educational reformer
4.He dedicated much of his life for the education of poor children in France.
5.He is considered the founder of the first Catholic schools.
6.Born in Reims, France.
7.Received the tonsure at age eleven and was named canon of Rheims Cathedral when he was fifteen
8.He was the patron of all teachers of youth.
9.First son of a wealthy parents living in France
10.In 1900 he was declared as a Saint. 


